cs.DC, cs.DB, cs.DS, cs.OS, cs.NI 

This paper is likely to belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category as it discusses a new causally consistent geo-replicated key-value store that leverages hybrid logical/physical clocks to achieve low latency and a new stabilization protocol that uses a combination of vector and scalar clocks to achieve higher resource efficiency and better availability. 

It could also belong to the Databases (cs.DB) sub-category as it deals with a key-value store and evaluates its performance with different workloads. 

The Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category is also a possibility as the paper discusses the implementation of a new stabilization protocol that uses a combination of vector and scalar clocks. 

The Operating Systems (cs.OS) sub-category is another possibility as the paper discusses the implementation of a new key-value store and its performance on Amazon AWS. 

Finally, the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category is a possibility as the paper discusses the implementation of a new causally consistent geo-replicated key-value store that achieves high performance.
